# Churchieum Development Rules

## Development Principles

Every feature and page must follow these principles:

| Principle | Requirement |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Responsive** | Support **PC**, **Tablet**, and **Mobile** on every page |
| **TypeScript** | Strict typing; no `any` unless unavoidable and documented |
| **Tailwind CSS** | Use design tokens (`src/styles/index.css`) and Tailwind utilities — avoid one-off inline styles when a token/class exists |
| **Component separation** | Split pages, layout shells, and reusable UI — no monolithic page files |
| **Reusability** | Extend `components/common/`, `components/layout/`, `hooks/`, `services/` before duplicating |

### Responsive (PC · Tablet · Mobile)

- Use `useBreakpoint()` (`hooks/useBreakpoint.ts`):
  - `isMobile` — &lt;768px (phone)
  - `isTablet` — 768–1023px
  - `isPc` — ≥1024px (desktop)
  - `isDesktop` / `isNotMobile` — ≥768px (tablet + PC shell: sidebar, wide layout)
- Wrap screens in `AppLayout` — desktop sidebar + mobile bottom nav pattern.
- **PC:** max content width **900px** (`PageContentWell`), card grid where appropriate.
- **Tablet:** same content well; avoid dense multi-column grids.
- **Mobile:** list/card layout, large tap targets (button height **56px**), bottom navigation.
- Test layout at ~375px, ~768px, and ≥1024px before shipping.

### TypeScript · Tailwind · Components

- Page files live in `src/pages/{member|admin|pastor|shared}/`.
- Layout shells live in `src/components/{member|pastor|admin}/Layout.tsx`.
- Shared UI: `components/common/ui/`, layout chrome: `components/layout/`.
- Business logic & storage: `src/services/` — not inside JSX.
- Types: `src/types/`; helpers: `src/utils/`; static data: `src/data/`.

## Design System (summary)

- **Colors:** Primary `#2563EB`, Secondary `#4F46E5`, Background `#F8FAFC`, Success `#16A34A`, Warning `#F59E0B`, Error `#DC2626`
- **Font:** Pretendard — Regular 400, SemiBold 600, Bold 700
- **Radius:** 16px (`rounded-card`, `rounded-btn`)
- **Button height:** 56px (`btn-primary`, `h-btn`, `ChurchButton` md/lg)
- **Philosophy:** Naver-like information structure + KidsNote warmth — large text, cards, generous spacing

## UI Principles

Every screen and interaction must follow these rules:

| Principle | Requirement |
|-----------|-------------|
| **한 화면 한 가지 목적** | One primary goal per screen — one hero action, no competing workflows |
| **메뉴 2단계 이하** | Navigation depth ≤ 2: e.g. 홈 → 기능 (no 홈 → 중간 → 하위 → 상세) |
| **버튼에 아이콘** | Every action button includes a Lucide icon (`ChurchButton` `icon` prop) |
| **클릭 영역 ≥ 48px** | All tappable targets: `min-h-[48px]` / `.touch-target` (primary buttons: **56px**) |
| **3초 이해** | Title + one-line subtitle visible immediately; plain Korean; no jargon |
| **자동 저장** | All form/input flows use debounced auto-save (`hooks/useAutoSave`) + localStorage fallback |

### 한 화면 한 가지 목적

- Page header states **what** and **why** in one line (`PageHeaderBar` subtitle).
- At most **one** primary button (`btn-primary` / `ChurchButton` variant `primary`).
- Secondary actions use `outline` / `ghost` — visually subordinate.

### 메뉴 2단계 이하

- Level 1: role home (`MemberHome`, `PastorHome`, `AdminHome`) or bottom/sidebar nav.
- Level 2: feature page (`PrayerPage`, `SermonPage`, …).
- Do **not** add nested hub pages; use tabs or in-page sections instead of deeper nav trees.

### 버튼 · 터치 · 이해하기 쉬운 UI

```tsx
import { Save } from 'lucide-react';
import { ChurchButton } from '../components/common/ui/ChurchButton';

<ChurchButton icon={<Save size={20} />} size="md">저장</ChurchButton>
```

- Icon + label together; icon-only buttons need `aria-label`.
- Use `touch-target` class for list rows, icon buttons, and chips.
- Empty states: icon + short Korean sentence + one clear next step.

### 자동 저장

- Use `useAutoSave(value, saveFn, { delayMs: 800 })` for text fields and forms.
- Persist to localStorage in demo mode; try Supabase in `saveFn` with `try/catch` fallback.
- Show subtle “저장됨” feedback — never block the user with a save dialog.

## Routing & Pages

- **Never break existing routing.** Navigation is state-based in `src/app/App.tsx` (`mode`, `memberPage`, `pastorPage`, `adminPage`). Do not replace with URL routing without an explicit migration plan.
- **Never remove existing pages** without user confirmation.
- Preserve invite URL handling (`?code=`, `?invite=`, `/invite/{code}`).

## Roles

- **Always preserve admin / pastor / member role separation.**
- `super_admin` → admin mode; `pastor` → pastor mode; `member` → member mode.
- Use `services/permissions.ts` and `AuthContext` (`isAdmin`, `isPastor`) — do not collapse roles into a single experience.

## Components & Layout

- **Prefer shared components** (`components/common/`, `components/layout/`) over duplicating layouts.
- Reuse `AppLayout`, `PageHeaderBar`, `EmptyState`, `TabBar`, `ChurchButton`, `ChurchCard`, and `HomeDashboard` patterns before creating one-off UI.

## Accessibility (Elderly Users)

- **Large fonts**, **clear buttons**, **simple words** — avoid IT/admin jargon.
- Short labels, one primary action per screen, generous tap targets on mobile.
- Desktop: **max content width 900px** unless the page truly needs full width (e.g. wide tables, bible reader).
- Mobile: **simple list/card layout** — avoid dense grids and nested navigation.

## Church Language (No Marketplace Tone)

Do not use marketplace/commerce language. Use these replacements:

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| 거래하기 | 함께 나누기 |
| 판매자 | 나눔교회 |
| 구매자 | 신청교회 |
| 판매완료 | 나눔완료 |
| 후기 | 감사나눔 |

Prefer: **나눔, 섬김, 교제, 기도, 은혜** — not 거래, 판매, 구매.

## Data & Resilience

- **Always keep localStorage demo fallback working.** Demo accounts and `churchieum_demo_user` must remain functional without a backend.
- **Supabase/Firebase failures must not break UI.** Never throw on missing env vars at import time; catch API errors and fall back to demo/localStorage data.
- Do not remove demo seed data or fallback paths when adding backend integration.

## Verification

- **Run `npm run build`** after important changes to ensure the app still bundles and renders.
